Name: Caledonian Ave & Railway Pde, Maylands
Risk Second: Poor or no provision for cyclists
Description: There's two sets of traffic lights either side of the railway, with the right turns on both set very short, so people have to rush to get through, high density traffic, coupled with a high speed bike path that cyclists don't have to stop for through car traffic (and don't!) ... I frequently have to madly stop in the trainlines or hit a cyclist or dodge a pedestrian - mad fast choices, all while traffic is desperate to get through before next train closes booms again.

Name: 51 & Seventh Ave, Maylands
Description: Key intersection feeding to and from the Seventh Avenue Bridge. However major issue with cars crossing Guildford Road to southern continuation of Seventh Avenue with little rest area/ median strip. Results in cars crossing four lanes of traffic at once with numerous accidents and near misses. Recommended to insert barrier to cars crossing directly to southern section of Seventh Avenue and instead inserting turn arrows for Guildford Avenue and Eighth Avenue to enable safer crossing.
Location: {"Sector": "", "PlaceName": "", "Territory": "", "Neighborhood": "Maylands", "CountryCode": "AUS", "District": "", "City": "Perth", "Region": "Western Australia", "Address": "51 & Seventh Ave", "AddNum": "", "ShortLabel": "51 & Seventh Ave", "Subregion": "", "LongLabel": "51 & Seventh Ave, Maylands", "PostalExt": "", "Match_addr": "51 & Seventh Ave, Maylands, Western Australia, 6051", "Postal": "6051", "Type": "", "Addr_type": "StreetInt", "Block": "", "MetroArea": ""}
Comment 1: I regularly come across traffic accidents at this intersection. And tragically, several years ago, one of the accidents involved the fatality of a young child.
Comment 2: Robyn: This intersection takes you to a bridge accross the railway line but has no turning support accross a very busy road. There have been a couple of deaths and many many accidents.
Comment 6: Clyde: Traffic crossing 7th Avenue from either side at risk of being hit by through traffic on Guildford Rd. A central median strip is required on Guildford Rd to stop traffic crossing  over fully from either direction. The creation of a central median strip on Guildford Rd would also prevent westbound traffic on Guildford Rd trying to turn right into 7th Avenue, especially during morning peak hours.

Name: 51 & Eighth Ave, Maylands
Description: Need for turning arrows from Guildford road into Eighth Avenue. Currently only option for turning in peak hour is at end of grren light risking orange light runners. Eighth Avenue is the main shopping street for Maylands and should have turning arrows to facilitate turning. Will also provide some relief for those turning into/from Seventh Avenue for the Seventh Avenue Bridge.
